comment._content: Notting Hill House, Belfast www.flickr.com/photos/gerryward/1717209254/ A Charles E Cooke, aged 26, born Belfast was a passenger on board a steam ship in Holyhead harbour on census night 1911. He was described as a Merchant's Clerk.
